properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 7 at 5:54AM AKST until January 7 at 3:00PM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow. New snow accumulation of 3 to 6 inches.

* WHERE...Portions of the northern Panhandle and eastern gulf
coast, including Gustavus, Pelican, and Elfin Cove.

* WHEN...Until 3 PM AKST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be difficult.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow showers will limit visibility at
times.
properties.instruction:
An advisory means that a potentially hazardous event is already
occurring or imminent.
